title: Zoe Lofgren
added: During the 2004, 2006 and 2008 elections, Lofgren's campaign paid approximately $350,000 to two businesses her husband operates: Collins and Day and John Marshall Collins P.C. over a six year period to support campaign efforts.<ref name="Coile">{{cite news |last1=Coile |first1=Zachary |title=Watchdog lists 64 in the House paying kin out campaign funds / It's legal, but some wonder whether it's good government |url=https://www.sfgate.com/politics/article/Watchdog-lists-64-in-the-House-paying-kin-out-2555377.php |accessdate=21 November 2020 |work=SFGATE |date=19 June 2007}}</ref>
